PLEASE READ CAREFULLY, AGREE TO EACH SECTION.



1. Students may elect to take no more than 8 units of credit/no credit courses toward the 32 units required for graduation. Students may take only 1 unit of CR/NC per semester. Taking a class credit/no credit will not affect the core, category or mode but may impact GPA calculations for admissions purposes at other institutions.
Q7: 2. The time period for submitting an application for credit/no credit grading begins with registration and ends at 5 pm on last class day of the semester. You are allowed to switch back to numerical grading at any point before 5 pm on the last class day.
Q8: 3. Final grades are officially recorded as "Credit" or "No Credit". You will only receive the "Credit" designation if your final grade is a 2.0 or higher. If your final grade is lower than a 2.0 you will receive the "No Credit" designation. Neither grade designation is figured into your grade point average. Only courses in which you receive the "Credit" designation will be added to your total units earned.
Q9: 4. Casses taken within your major/minor may not be taken as credit/no credit without prior approval from the department.
Q10: 5. Medical, professional and graduate programs require courses to be taken for a grade. LSDAS, Law School Admissions Council computes NC as grades of failure.
